ref:Type.name: String
ref:Type.description: String is a global object that may be used to construct String instances.

members.name: fromCharCode
members.description:
Static method that returns a string created from the specified sequence of UTF-16 code units.
String.fromCharCode(0x2014); // returns "—"
String.fromCharCode(65, 66, 67); // returns "ABC"

@param {Number...} num A sequence of numbers that are UTF-16 code units. The range is between 0 and 65535 (0xFFFF). Numbers greater than 0xFFFF are truncated. No validity checks are performed.

@return String A string of length N consisting of the N specified UTF-16 code units.

members.name: fromCodePoint
members.description:
Static method that returns a string created by using the specified sequence of code points. String.fromCharCode() cannot return supplementary characters (i.e. code points 0x010000 – 0x10FFFF) by specifying their code point. Instead, it requires the UTF-16 surrogate pair for that. String.fromCodePoint(), on the other hand, can return 4-byte supplementary characters, as well as the more common 2-byte BMP characters, by specifying their code point (which is equivalent to the UTF-32 code unit). RangeError is thrown if an invalid Unicode code point is given (e.g. "RangeError: NaN is not a valid code point").
String.fromCodePoint(42); // "*"
String.fromCodePoint(65, 90); // "AZ"
String.fromCodePoint(0x2f804); // "\uD87E\uDC04"
String.fromCodePoint(-1); // RangeError
String.fromCodePoint(3.14); // RangeError

@param {Number...} num A sequence of code points.

@return String A string created by using the specified sequence of code points.

members.name: padEnd
members.description:
The padEnd() method pads the current string with a given string (repeated, if needed) so that the resulting string reaches a given length. The padding is applied from the end of the current string.
string.padEnd(10, '*');

@param {Number} targetLength The length of the resulting string once the current str has been padded. If the value is less than or equal to str.length, then str is returned as-is.
@param {String} [padString] The string to pad the current str with. If padString is too long to stay within the targetLength, it will be truncated from the end. The default value is the unicode "space" character (U+0020).

@return String A String of the specified targetLength with the padString applied at the end of the current str.

members.name: padStart
members.description:
The padStart() method pads the current string with another string (multiple times, if needed) until the resulting string reaches the given length. The padding is applied from the start of the current string.
string.padStart(10, '*');

@param {Number} targetLength The length of the resulting string once the current str has been padded. If the value is less than or equal to str.length, then str is returned as-is.
@param {String} [padString] The string to pad the current str with. If padString is too long to stay within the targetLength, it will be truncated from the end. The default value is the unicode "space" character (U+0020).

@return String A String of the specified targetLength with padString applied from the start.

members.name: elements
members.description: When the elements method is called with one parameter name, it returns an XMLList containing all the children of this XML object that are XML elements with the given name. When the elements method is called with no parameters, it returns an XMLList containing all the children of this XML object that are XML elements regardless of their name.

members.name: hasComplexContent
members.description: The hasComplexContent method returns a Boolean value indicating whether this XML object contains complex content. An XML object is considered to contain complex content if it represents an XML element that has child elements. XML objects representing attributes, comments, processing instructions and text nodes do not have complex content. The existence of attributes, comments, processing instructions and text nodes within an XML object is not significant in determining if it has complex content.

members.name: hasOwnProperty
members.description: The hasOwnProperty method returns a Boolean value indicating whether this object has the property specified by P. For all XML objects except the XML prototype object, this is the same result returned by the internal method [[HasProperty]]. For the XML prototype object, hasOwnProperty also examines the list of local properties to determine if there is a method property with the given name.

members.name: hasSimpleContent
members.description: The hasSimpleContent method returns a Boolean value indicating whether this XML object contains simple content. An XML object is considered to contain simple content if it represents a text node, represents an attribute node or if it represents an XML element that has no child elements. XML objects representing comments and processing instructions do not have simple content. The existence of attributes, comments, processing instructions and text nodes within an XML object is not significant in determining if it has simple content.

members.name: inScopeNamespaces
members.description: The inScopeNamespaces method returns an Array of Namespace objects representing the namespaces in scope for this XML object in the context of its parent. If the parent of this XML object is modified, the associated namespace declarations may change. The set of namespaces returned by this method may be a super set of the namespaces used by this value.

members.name: insertChildAfter
members.description: The insertChildAfter method inserts the given child2 after the given child1 in this XML object and returns this XML object. If child1 is null, the insertChildAfter method inserts child2 before all children of this XML object (i.e., after none of them). If child1 does not exist in this XML object, it returns without modifying this XML object.

members.name: insertChildBefore
members.description: The insertChildBefore method inserts the given child2 before the given child1 in this XML object and returns this XML object. If child1 is null, the insertChildBefore method inserts child2 after all children in this XML object (i.e., before none of them). If child1 does not exist in this XML object, it returns without modifying this XML object.

members.name: length
members.description: The length method always returns the integer 1 for XML objects. This treatment intentionally blurs the distinction between a single XML object and an XMLList containing only one value

members.name: name
members.description: The name method returns the qualified name (QName) associated with this XML object

members.name: namespace
members.description: If no prefix is specified, the namespace method returns the Namespace associated with the qualified name of this XML object. If a prefix is specified, the namespace method looks for a namespace in scope for this XML object with the given prefix and, if found, returns it. If no such namespace is found, the namespace method returns undefined

members.name: namespaceDeclarations

members.name: normalize
members.description: The normalize method puts all text nodes in this and all descendant XML objects into a normal form by merging adjacent text nodes and eliminating empty text nodes. It returns this XML object.

members.name: parent
members.description: The parent method returns the parent of this XML object.

members.name: prependChild
members.description: The prependChild method inserts the given child into this object prior to its existing XML properties and returns this XML object.

members.name: processingInstructions
members.description: When the processingInstructions method is called with one parameter name, it returns an XMLList containing all the children of this XML object that are processing-instructions with the given name. When the processingInstructions method is called with no parameters, it returns an XMLList containing all the children of this XML object that are processing-instructions regardless of their name

members.name: propertyIsEnumerable
members.description: The propertyIsEnumerable method returns a Boolean value indicating whether the property P will be included in the set of properties iterated over when this XML object is used in a for-in statement. This method returns truewhen ToString(P) is "0"; otherwise, it returns false. This treatment intentionally blurs the distinction between a single XML object and an XMLList containing only one value

members.name: removeNamespace
members.description: The removeNamespace method removes the given namespace from the in scope namespaces of this object and all its descendents, then returns a copy of this XML object. The removeNamespaces method will not remove a namespace from an object where it is referenced by that object�s QName or the QNames of that object�s attributes

members.name: replace
members.description: The replace method replaces the XML properties of this XML object specified by propertyName with value and returns this XML object. If this XML object contains no properties that match propertyName, the replace method returns without modifying this XML object. The propertyName parameter may be a numeric property name, an unqualified name for a set of XML elements, a qualified name for a set of XML elements or the properties wildcard "*". When the propertyName parameter is an unqualified name, it identifies XML elements in the default namespace. The value parameter may be an XML object, XMLList object or any value that may be converted to a String with ToString().

members.name: setChildren
members.description: The setChildren method replaces the XML properties of this XML object with a new set of XML properties from value. value may be a single XML object or an XMLList. setChildren returns this XML object.

members.name: setLocalName
members.description: The setLocalName method replaces the local name of this XML object with a string constructed from the givenname

members.name: setName
members.description: The setName method replaces the name of this XML object with a QName or AttributeName constructed from the given name

members.name: setNamespace
members.description: The setNamespace method replaces the namespace associated with the name of this XML object with the given namespace

members.name: text
members.description: The text() method represents the source code of an object.

members.name: toString
members.description: Returns a String value for this object.

members.name: toXMLString
members.description: Returns a String value for this object.

members.name: valueOf
members.description: The valueOf method returns this XML object

members.name: attribute
members.description: The attribute method returns an XMLList containing zero or one XML attributes associated with this XML object that have the given attributeName.

members.name: attributes
members.description: The attributes method returns an XMLList containing the XML attributes of this object.

members.name: child
members.description: The child method returns the list of children in this XML object matching the given propertyName.

members.name: children
members.description: The children method returns an XMLList containing all the properties of this XML object in order

members.name: comments
members.description: The comments method returns an XMLList containing the properties of this XML object that represent XML comments.

members.name: copy
members.description: The copy method returns a deep copy of this XML object with the internal [[Parent]] property set to null.

members.name: descendants
members.description: The descendants method returns all the XML valued descendants (children, grandchildren, great-grandchildren, etc.) of this XML object with the given name. If the name parameter is omitted, it returns all descendants of this XML object.

members.name: elements
members.description: When the elements method is called with one parameter name, it returns an XMLList containing all the children of this XML object that are XML elements with the given name. When the elements method is called with no parameters, it returns an XMLList containing all the children of this XML object that are XML elements regardless of their name.

members.name: hasComplexContent
members.description: The hasComplexContent method returns a Boolean value indicating whether this XML object contains complex content. An XML object is considered to contain complex content if it represents an XML element that has child elements. XML objects representing attributes, comments, processing instructions and text nodes do not have complex content. The existence of attributes, comments, processing instructions and text nodes within an XML object is not significant in determining if it has complex content.

members.name: hasOwnProperty
members.description: The hasOwnProperty method returns a Boolean value indicating whether this object has the property specified by P. For all XML objects except the XML prototype object, this is the same result returned by the internal method [[HasProperty]]. For the XML prototype object, hasOwnProperty also examines the list of local properties to determine if there is a method property with the given name.

members.name: hasSimpleContent
members.description: The hasSimpleContent method returns a Boolean value indicating whether this XML object contains simple content. An XML object is considered to contain simple content if it represents a text node, represents an attribute node or if it represents an XML element that has no child elements. XML objects representing comments and processing instructions do not have simple content. The existence of attributes, comments, processing instructions and text nodes within an XML object is not significant in determining if it has simple content.

members.name: length
members.description: The length method always returns the integer 1 for XML objects. This treatment intentionally blurs the distinction between a single XML object and an XMLList containing only one value

members.name: stringify
members.description: Convert a value to JSON, optionally replacing values if a replacer function is specified, or optionally including only the specified properties if a replacer array is specified. The optional space causes the resulting string to be pretty-printed.

ref:GenericType.name: Map
ref:GenericType.description: The Map object holds key-value pairs and remembers the original insertion order of the keys. Any value (both objects and primitive values) may be used as either a key or a value

members.name: size
members.description: The size accessor property returns the number of elements in a Map object.

members.name: set
members.description: The set() method adds or updates an entry in a Map object with a specified key and a value.

members.name: get
members.description: The get() method returns a specified element from a Map object. If the value that is associated to the provided key is an object, then you will get a reference to that object and any change made to that object will effectively modify it inside the Map object.

members.name: clear
members.description: The clear() method removes all elements from a Map object.

members.name: delete
members.description: The delete() method removes the specified element from a Map object by key.

members.name: entries
members.description: The entries() method returns a new iterator object that contains the [key, value] pairs for each element in the Map object in insertion order. In this particular case, this iterator object is also an iterable, so the for-of loop can be used.

members.name: forEach
members.description: The forEach() method executes a provided function once per each key/value pair in the Map object, in insertion order.

members.name: has
members.description: The has() method returns a boolean indicating whether an element with the specified key exists or not.

members.name: keys
members.description: The keys() method returns a new iterator object that contains the keys for each element in the Map object in insertion order. In this particular case, this iterator object is also an iterable, so a for...of loop can be used.

members.name: values
members.description: The values() method returns a new iterator object that contains the values for each element in the Map object in insertion order.

ref:GenericType.name: Set
ref:GenericType.description: The Set object lets you store unique values of any type, whether primitive values or object references

members.name: size
members.description: The size accessor property returns the number of elements in a Set object.

members.name: add
members.description: The add() method inserts a new element with a specified value in to a Set object, if there isn't an element with the same value already in the Set

members.name: clear
members.description: The clear() method removes all elements from a Set object.

members.name: delete
members.description: The delete() method removes a specified value from a Set object, if it is in the set. Returns true if value was already in Set; otherwise false.

members.name: entries
members.description: The entries() method returns a new Iterator object that contains an array of [value, value] for each element in the Set object, in insertion order. For Set objects there is no key like in Map objects. However, to keep the API similar to the Map object, each entry has the same value for its key and value here, so that an array [value, value] is returned

members.name: forEach
members.description: The forEach() method executes a provided function once for each value in the Set object, in insertion order.

members.name: has
members.description: The has() method returns a boolean indicating whether an element with the specified value exists in a Set object or not

members.name: keys
members.description: The keys() method is an alias for the values() method.

members.name: values
members.description: The values() method returns a new Iterator object that contains the values for each element in the Set object in insertion order

ref:GenericType.name: Iterator
ref:GenericType.description: An iterator is an object which defines a sequence and potentially a return value upon its termination

members.name: next
members.description: Returns the next IterableValue for this Iterable

ref:GenericType.name: IterableValue
ref:GenericType.description: A value object that the Iterator.next() object will return

members.name: value
members.description: the value for this iterable object

members.name: done
members.description: a boolean telling if this was the last one (true) or not (false)
